{"title_page": "Focus FM (Ghana)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Radio Station\n| name = Focus FM\n| image = \n| city = [[Kumasi]]\n| area = [[Ashanti Region]]\n| branding = \n| slogan = \n| airdate = \n| frequency = 94.3&nbsp;MHz,\n| format = Local news, talk and music\n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| power = \n| erp = \n| class = \n| callsign_meaning = \n| owner = [[KNUST]]\n| website = [https://focusnewsroom.com Focusnewsroom.com]\n| coordinates = \n}}\n\n'''Focus FM''' is the official [[campus radio]] station of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] located in the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/directory/focus-fm|title=Focus FM|date=2016-02-25|website=Music In Africa|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yesghanaonline.com/station/focus-fm/|title=Focus FM|website=Yes Ghana Online|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> The '''station''' is owned and run by the office of the University Relations Office.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rawgist.com/focus-fm-should-be-the-clearing-house-for-all-knust-related-news-dean-of-students/|title=Focus FM should be the clearing house for all KNUST-related news-Dean of Students|last=Buachi/rawgist.com|first=Bernard|date=2017-10-21|website=Raw Gist|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nFocus FM was established in the year 2000 A.D by the office of the University Relations Office of the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology. The Student Representative Council,  the Graduate Student Association of Ghana of the University and the University are the stakeholders of Focus FM.\nThe core objectives for the establishment of the station was to inform, educate and entertain the entire university community and its surrounding communities and to provide a platform for local arts, musical, literary, sports, and other cultural activities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rawgist.com/brief-history-information-on-focus-fm-ghana/|title=BRIEF HISTORY/ INFORMATION ON FOCUS FM (Ghana)|last=Rawgist|date=2016-01-20|website=Raw Gist|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rawgist.com/focus-fm-journalists-win-big-at-knust-eminence-awards/|title=Focus FM Journalists win big at KNUST Eminence awards|last=Essien|first=John|date=2020-02-08|website=Raw Gist|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/Kumasi-showcases-rap-talents-at-Focus-FM-event-251481|title=Kumasi showcases rap talents at Focus FM event|website=ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://focusfmknust.wordpress.com/2012/07/06/focus-fm-to-host-this-years-edition-of-face-of-shs-talent-and-beauty-hunt/|title=FOCUS FM TO HOST THIS YEAR'S EDITION OF FACE OF SHS TALENT AND BEAUTY HUNT|date=2012-07-06|website=FOCUS NEWS|language=en|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\n== List of Journalists who passed through Focus FM ==\nFocus FM is proud of its legacy of illumni active in journalism. Past presenters include.\n\n* [[Edward Oppong Marfo]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rawgist.com/edward-oppong-marfo-joins-citi-fm-as-bureau-chief-for-the-middle-belt/|title=Edward Oppong Marfo joins Citi FM as Bureau Chief for the Middle belt|last=Rawgist.com|date=2018-11-08|website=Raw Gist|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref>\n* [[Kwame Adinkra]]\n* [[DJ Aroma]]\n* [[Louis Kwame Sakyiamah]] (Lexis Bill)\n*[[Nana Jantuah]]\n*Bernard Buachi\n* Kojo Akoto Boateng\n* Nathaniel Osei Kuffuor (Mahony)\n* Mina Dablu\n* Gemma Appiah\n* DJ Sleem\n*Ebenezer Nana Yaw Donkor (NYDJ)\n*Mensah Junior\n*David Apinga\n*[[John Essien]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://todaysprofile.com/2020/02/08/focus-fms-john-essien-wins-outstanding-student-journalist-at-maiden-knust-eminent-awards/|title=John Essien is KNUST Eminence Awards Outstanding Student Journalist of the year|last=Essie